Preconditions:
- The `processorTime` list must not be null.
- The `tasks` list must not be null.
- The `processorTime` list must have at least one element.
- The `tasks` list must have at least one element.
- The `processorTime` list must only contain non-negative integers.
- The `tasks` list must only contain non-negative integers.
- The length of the `processorTime` list must be equal to the length of the `tasks` list.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the minimum time when all tasks have been executed by the processors.
- The returned value is non-negative.
- The returned value is the minimum possible time to execute all tasks.
- The original `processorTime` list and `tasks` list remain unchanged after the method is called.